Differential diagnosis.
Externally the species is closely similar to 

M. namakwanus

(
Fig. 6
) however, it can be easily distinguished by the following combinations of characteristics: irregular punctuation of pronotum disc (
Fig. 62
), elytral interstriae shagreened and covered by small shiny tubercles (
Fig. 72
), the sclerite of the internal sac of the aedeagus curved basely with a small lateral process (
Fig. 26
).

Habitat and distribution. This species was collected from a few localities occupying a small distribution range in the southwest of Western Cape Province ( Fig. 2 ). Based on (
Olson et al. 2001
) terrestrial ecoregions of the world, the range of this species comprises the southwest part of the moister Fynbos and Renosterveld ecoregion and part of the montane Fynbos and Renosterveld in Cedarberg.
